The paper proposes a method for efficient and accurate traffic speed prediction using Gaussian processes and big traffic data obtained from static sensors. This work involves machine learning techniques such as non-negative matrix factorization and GP kernel functions to model road network topology and incorporate side information. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, since the paper addresses the problem of efficient traffic speed prediction, it could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
